Key Match Events: Rohit Sharma scored 92 runs, including 76 in boundaries, helping India to 205/5.
Josh Hazlewood conceded only 14 runs in his 4 overs, with India scoring 71 runs off his 24 balls.
Travis Head fell for 76, contributing significantly to Australia's 181/7.
Axar Patel made a sensational catch to dismiss Glenn Maxwell for 21, breaking a 81-run partnership.
Hardik Pandya hit three sixes in the final two overs to push India's total past 200.
Post-Match Reflections: Rohit Sharma's performance was pivotal in India's victory and advancement to the semi-finals.
Travis Head's performance was crucial for Australia, but his fall left them struggling.
Miscellaneous Highlights: India scored 10 fours and 10 sixes while Rohit was at the crease, managing only 9 combined after his fall.
Josh Hazlewood's strategy of bowling on lengths helped control Rohit's shots effectively.
Axar Patel's catch was a turning point in the match, breaking a promising partnership.
Glenn Maxwell was dismissed by Kuldeep Yadav with a googly, which was described as needing to be framed.
